<br>
Well actually you are mistaken i think, PA bonus does scale with weapon damage. PA bonus is calculated upon % of the base damage at higher cons. That means if you have a low base damage, you have a low pa too. Thats why you get a lesser perforate at higher cons, if that wouldnt be true i would get +480 dmg from perforate on purple mobs.<br>
<br>
If you have a lower weaponskill, you have a low base weapon damage, thus you get a lower bonus from perforate.<br>
<br>
If you have a high weaponskill, you will benefit from the high % bonus of perforate.<br>
<br>
I.e.<br>
<br>
low weapon skill = 50 dmg + 200% pa (from base dmg) = 150 dmg<br>
high weapon skill = 100 dmg + 200% pa (from base dmg) = 300 dmg<br>
<br>
200% was just a wild guess just to show you an example.<br>
<br>
The lower your base damage on a target is, the lower your perforate is. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=majin>Majin</A> at: 2/1/02 1:50:05 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/usunthasbayne.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sunthas Bayne</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/1/02 4:18:39 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1992.topic&index=14>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.webpak.net/~njb/emblemsm.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: PA damage, mid 30s for Nightshades.  Poll, and observati</span><hr size=1> Don't you think it would make more sense that PA damage scales with mob level and armor type rather than weapon damage?<br>
