<br>
Oh, and heroes will tend to have higher weaponskill than us.  This because there's a very good chance they're maxed on weapon spec, and that they're on a pure strength based weapon, which they tend to have tons of.  If we had a speccable pure dex base weapon, and it was desireable to full spec in it, we'd have equivalent weaponskill to heroes.  <br>
As is, I'm really not entirely sure how weaponskill is derived.  I know that spec points in your weapon will raise weaponskill, as will additional stat points in whatever the weapon base stat is.  Right now, with buffs my weaponskill is in the mid 500s I think (I added a ton of +str items recently.. Think I'm capping now though), and with items my natural strength is 96 or so...  Okay, it's still 20 or so shy of dex, but it's enough to make the strength base of my weapons not hurt quite as much.   (Sad thing is, I now have to choose between 3 neckpieces.  Rogue Overlord Pendant, with a +1 to stealth, Master Assassin Pendant, with +2 to envenom, and Noble Lord's Pendant (Or somethign like), with +7 to Str and Con...)<br>
