<br>
When you do hit your cap the (+xxx) part will be very high, probably because it was your actual roll with mob level included then your cap kicked in. If you take actual damage minus base damage you will get your style (or critical strike) damage. <br>
<br>
If you then go kill a blue mob you should see the same percentage of styledamage over base damage. Do a purple, and you should continue to see ever smaller numbers but same percentage of style damage over base damage.<br>
<br>
Change weapons and the style damage numbers should be about the same (depending on delay for normal styles) but your based damage would change according to your new weapon. <br>
